{"title": "Ways of St. Anthony", "description": "Saint Anthony of Padua is especially invoked and venerated all over the world as the patron saint for the recovery of lost items and is credited with many miracles involving lost people, lost things and even lost spiritual goods.<br><br>\n\nThe names and places in these stories are fiction; the incidents, however, are real. They were sent to the Editor by clients of the Saint in their accounts of thanksgivings for favors received through St. Anthony's intercession and for which most of them had promised publication. The writer has simply woven these accounts into readable stories.  (From the book)\n", "duration": 7416, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "15463", "name": "Sister M. Josephine"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/waysofstanthony_2101_librivox/waysstanthony_2102.jpg", "copyright_year": "1922", "genres": ["Christianity - Other"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Maria Therese"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Maria Therese"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Maria Therese"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "St. Anthony and the Crucifix", "readers": [8425], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/waysofstanthony_2101_librivox/waysofstanthony_01_josephine_64kb.mp3", "duration": 405}, {"section": 2, "title": "St. Anthony and the Diamond", "readers": [6836], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/waysofstanthony_2101_librivox/waysofstanthony_02_josephine_64kb.mp3", "duration": 363}, {"section": 3, "title": "St. Anthony as a Lawyer", "readers": [6836], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/waysofstanthony_2101_librivox/waysofstanthony_03_josephine_64kb.mp3", "duration": 539}, {"section": 4, "title": "St. Anthony and the Ford", "readers": [6836], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/waysofstanthony_2101_librivox/waysofstanthony_04_josephine_64kb.mp3", "duration": 459}, {"section": 5, "title": "St